name: ImmunocompromisedConditions
title: Immunocompromised Conditions
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains diagnoses most commonly used for patients with Immunocompromising  conditions.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who have an active  diagnosis of an immunocompromising condition. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the Diagnosis category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Inlcude codes representing a diagnosis of  immunocompromising conditions including leukemia, lymphocytic leukemia, lymphoma, marked neutropenia, myelogenic leukemia, myeloma, myelodysplasia, pancytopenia, and significant neutropenia using the ICD 9 CM code system.),(Exclusion Criteria: None.)
